{
  "id": "q-x402-payment-verification",
  "question": "How should a paid API verify and settle an x402 payment on Stellar?",
  "surface": [
    "skills.stellar-dev.agentic-payments",
    "stellarDocs.search_docs"
  ],
  "golden": {
    "answer": "In the current Stellar x402 scheme, the client signs a Soroban authorization entry for an exact SAC transfer and a facilitator or relayer submits it; this is not necessarily a classic payment operation from the user. Verify scheme/version, CAIP network, token contract, parties, amount, exact invocation/auth shape, expiration, simulation, unexpected effects, final successful settlement, and request-level idempotency/replay binding before fulfillment. A Horizon operation-list match is insufficient for an inner contract transfer: post-settlement audit must decode successful transaction meta/events and exact SAC effects. As of 2026-07-11, Built on Stellar offers a hosted facilitator and OpenZeppelin a self-hosted plugin; neither is mandatory.",
    "keyFacts": [
      "The current Stellar x402 scheme signs a Soroban authorization entry for an exact SAC transfer that a facilitator or relayer submits.",
      "Verification covers scheme/version, CAIP network, invocation/auth shape, expiration, simulation, unexpected effects, finality, and request-level replay/idempotency.",
      "A Horizon operation-list match is insufficient for an inner contract transfer; audit successful transaction meta/events and exact SAC effects.",
      "Built on Stellar hosted and OpenZeppelin self-hosted facilitator paths are current attributed options as of 2026-07-11, not protocol requirements."
    ],
    "avoid": [
      "Possession of any Stellar transaction hash proves the required x402 payment.",
      "Checking only the asset code and amount is sufficient payment verification."
    ],
    "notes": "Status-sensitive details are stated as of 2026-07-11; grade later sourced changes leniently and require dated primary evidence."
  },
